==Most prominent summits==
{{see also|List of the ultra-prominent summits of Hawaii}}
Of the 13 major summits of Hawai{{okina}}i, Mauna Kea exceeds {{convert|4000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic prominence, Haleakalā exceeds {{convert|3000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}}, Mauna Loa exceeds {{convert|2000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}}, [[List of Ultras of Oceania#Hawai'i|six peaks are ultra-prominent summits with more than {{convert|1500|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}}]], and eight peaks exceed {{convert|1000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic prominence.
{{clear}}
