{{For|the moth genus|Mellona (moth)}} {{wiktionary|Mellona}} '''Mellona''' or '''Mellonia''' was an [[List of Roman deities|ancient Roman goddess]] said by [[Augustine of Hippo|St. Augustine]] to promote the supply of [[honey]] (Latin ''mel, mellis''), as [[Pomona (mythology)|Pomona]] did for apples and [[Bubona]] for cattle. <ref>[[Augustine of Hippo|Augustine]], ''De civitate Dei'' 4.34; [[Hendrik Wagenvoort]], "Diva Angerona," in ''Pietas: Selected Studies in Roman Religion'' (Brill, 1980), p. 22.</ref> [[Arnobius]] describes her as "a goddess important and powerful regarding bees, taking care of and protecting the sweetness of honey."<ref>[[Arnobius]], ''Adversus Nationes'', IV. 7 ''(Mellonia dea est pollens potensque in apibus, mellis curans custodiensque dulcedinem)'' and 8.</ref>
[[Wilhelm Heinrich Roscher|W.H. Roscher]] includes Mellona among the ''[[indigitamenta]]'', the list of deities maintained by Roman priests to assure that the correct divinity was invoked for rituals.<ref>[[Wilhelm Heinrich Roscher|W.H. Roscher]], ''Ausführliches Lexikon der griechischen und römischen Mythologie'' (Leipzig: Teubner, 1890–94), vol. 2, pt. 1, p. 203.</ref>
==See also== * [[Ah-Muzen-Cab]] -- [[Maya civilization|Mayan]] god of bees. * [[Aristaeus]] -- [[Ancient Greek]] god of bees. * [[List of Lithuanian mythological figures#Jan Łasicki|Austėja]] -- [[Lithuania]]n—goddess of bees. * [[Bhramari]] -- [[Hindu]] goddess of bees. * [[List of Lithuanian mythological figures#Jan Łasicki|Bubilas]] -- [[Lithuania]]n—god of bees. * [[List of Maya gods and supernatural beings#C|Colel Cab]] -- Mayan goddess of bees. * [[Melissa]] -- [[Ancient Greek]]/[[Minoan civilization|Minoan]]—goddess of bees. * [[Bee (mythology)]]
